}}}}super sonic phil{{{{ Killer kind show. That Tom Thumbs is so sick, with Jerry and Brent's mezmerizing jams. That song is a cousin to She belongs To Me. The way Jerry times out those sweet solos and Brent right behind him in a psychedelic blur. Terrapin,Music,birdsong, Morning Dew(so beautiful) Superstious is hot Jerry solos rip hard. Jerry bends some nice notes on Cold Rain.  Comes A Time is so out there Jerry sounds lost in his own persian haze "you get so far away from how it feels inside". gOoNeY bIrdSOnG
 Summer '85 was smoking, Iam talking cream of the crop quality Dead. Greek,Alpine,River bend and Blossom in Ohio were both awesome. Saratoga, Hershey and the best run played this year at Merriweather. These shows are some of the Deads finest playin. These were the days, the scene on this tour must of been a blast.  
 If your still searching for prime time '85 check out the Spectrum shows from the spring.
